en: Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) is a stylesheet language used to describe the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML. It also describes how elements should be rendered on screen, on paper, in speech, or on other media.

HTML (Hypertext Markup Language) is a text-based approach to describing how content contained within an HTML file is structured. This markup tells a web browser how to display text, images and other forms of multimedia on a webpage.

TypeScript is a free and open source programming language developed and maintained by Microsoft. It is a strict syntactical superset of JavaScript and adds optional static typing to the language. It is designed for the development of large applications and transpiles to JavaScript.
